==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gliff
<hw>Gliff</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OE.
<ets>gliffen</ets>, <ets>gliften</ets>, to look with fear at.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A transient glance; an unexpected view of something
that startles one; a sudden fear.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. &
Scot.]</mark> <rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A moment: as, for a <xex>gliff</xex>.</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glike</ent>⟦br⟧
